LAKEWOOD COGENERATION, L.P.
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Lakewood Cogeneration, L.P. ("Lakewood") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from its 246 MW combined-cycle gas-fired electric generation facility located in Lakewood, New Jersey to the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") system. This Rate Schedule sets forth Lakewood's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Supply Service to PJM, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. REACTIVE SUPPLY SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT Total Annual Revenue Requirement is $767,158 Total Monthly Revenue Requirement is $63,930
